## Migration from Chalice (Backward Compatibility)

### 1. Route Naming (DO NOT CHANGE)

```python
# ✅ CORRECT — Preserve Chalice route paths
@router.post("/CFDI/search")  # Was: @bp.route("/search", methods=["POST"])
@router.post("/Company/upload_cer")
@router.get("/status")

# ❌ WRONG — Breaking frontend
@router.post("/cfdi/search")  # Frontend expects "/CFDI/search"
```

### 2. Response Format (CRITICAL)

```python
# ✅ CORRECT — Chalice-compatible error shape
{
    "Code": "BadRequestError",
    "Message": "RFC is required"
}

# ❌ WRONG — FastAPI default (breaks frontend)
{
    "detail": "RFC is required"
}
```

### 3. Request Body Access

```python
# ✅ CORRECT — FastAPI async body parsing
@router.post("/endpoint")
async def endpoint(json_body: dict = Depends(get_json_body)):
    # get_json_body handles GET (empty dict) vs POST (await request.json())
    ...

# ❌ WRONG — Chalice pattern (no longer works)
@bp.route("/endpoint", methods=["POST"])
def endpoint():
    json_body = bp.current_request.json_body  # bp no longer exists
```

### 4. Dependency Injection Migration

```python
# ✅ BEFORE (Chalice SuperBlueprint)
@bp.route("/search", methods=["POST"])
def search(session, user, company_session):  # Auto-injected by parameter name
    return CFDIController.search(..., session=company_session)

# ✅ AFTER (FastAPI Depends)
@router.post("/search")
def search(
    json_body: dict = Depends(get_json_body),
    company_session: Session = Depends(get_company_session),
):
    return CFDIController.search(..., session=company_session)
```

